WEBVTT

00:00:00.150 --> 00:00:02.150
You'll notice the dates are messy and

00:00:02.150 --> 00:00:04.670
lack uniformity, leading to inconsistency

00:00:04.670 --> 00:00:05.590
across your data

00:00:08.905 --> 00:00:10.785
Highlight the cells containing dates you

00:00:10.785 --> 00:00:11.825
wish to format

00:00:12.019 --> 00:00:14.019
Right click on your selection and a menu

00:00:14.019 --> 00:00:16.579
will appear. Choose 'Format Cells'

00:00:17.139 --> 00:00:19.579
A dialog box will pop up with various

00:00:19.579 --> 00:00:21.539
formatting options. Here you can

00:00:21.539 --> 00:00:24.219
customize fonts, styles, colors,

00:00:24.219 --> 00:00:25.419
alignment, and more.

00:00:26.059 --> 00:00:27.939
From the category list on the left,

00:00:27.939 --> 00:00:28.659
select date.

00:00:29.115 --> 00:00:31.075
You will see a variety of date formats

00:00:31.075 --> 00:00:33.275
under the Type section. Scroll through

00:00:33.275 --> 00:00:35.555
the options and select the date format

00:00:35.555 --> 00:00:37.795
that best suits your needs. You can

00:00:37.795 --> 00:00:39.635
choose from options that display the date

00:00:39.635 --> 00:00:42.395
in full, abbreviate months, or even show

00:00:42.395 --> 00:00:43.915
only the month and year.

00:00:44.846 --> 00:00:47.446
For more specific needs, click on Custom.

00:00:47.726 --> 00:00:49.926
Here you can manually enter a format

00:00:49.926 --> 00:00:51.566
using the custom format codes.

00:00:51.950 --> 00:00:54.270
Click OK to apply the changes. The

00:00:54.270 --> 00:00:56.310
selected cells will now display dates in

00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:57.470
the format you've chosen.
